        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 4:18PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 25 miles northeast of Ridgeway to 8
miles west of Alzada, moving east southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alzada, Albion and Capitol.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
